cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Pub.Crawl — A Local Research Feed Reader"
message: "If you use Pub.Crawl, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Heineck
    given-names: Paul
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"   # ← deine ORCID eintragen
repository-code: "https://github.com/paulheineck/readr"
url: "https://github.com/paulheineck/readr"
abstract: >-
  Pub.Crawl is a local web app that aggregates
  journal RSS feeds for researchers. It lets you skim, star, and organize new
  papers in a swipeable card-stack interface, with full abstracts and clean
  author metadata pulled from CrossRef/OpenAlex, Open-Access (Unpaywall) and
  citation tools, a local relevance ranking learned from your likes/skips, and
  a curated catalog of psychology journal feeds.
keywords:
  - current awareness
  - literature monitoring
  - feed reader
  - RSS
  - psychology
  - open science
  - research tools
